-- Dundee’s Goodman Says Mining Industry Slump to Last 5 to 6 Years
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   D o n v i l l e   a n d   E r i c   L a m
-- 2013-03-05T18:45:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-05/dundee-s-goodman-says-mining-industry-slump-to-last-5-to-6-years.html
Dundee Corp. Chief Executive Officer
Ned Goodman said he expects the  mining industry  to remain in a
“bear market” for another five to six years.  Goodman spoke about his outlook for a continuing industry
slump today in a panel discussion at the Prospectors &
Developers Association of Canada  convention  in Toronto.  To contact the reporters on this story:
